   By QUENTIN PEEL
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Deutsche Aerospace (Dasa), the Daimler-Benz subsidiary which includes most
of Germany's key aerospace contractors, is to cut its workforce by 7,500 in
the next two years because of reduced orders, writes Quentin Peel. The cuts,
more than 10 per cent of the 70,000 employees in companies ranging from
Deutsche Airbus to MBB and MTU, will affect all main divisions.
