FT  08 OCT 92 / World News in Brief: Bomb explodes in central London
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
A small bomb, placed behind a telephone junction box, exploded near
Tottenham Court Road in central London. Several people were treated for
shock. Police said damage was minimal. Early yesterday a device in a litter
bin exploded near Piccadilly Circus slightly injuring five people.
