<HEADLINE>
FT  07 OCT 92 / International Company News: Bell Canada, GTE venture
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By BERNARD SIMON
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   TORONTO
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
GTE and Bell Canada, respectively the biggest local telephone companies in
the US and Canada, are to co-operate in selling their billing and other
information services to telephone utilities in other countries.
The two groups see lucrative opportunities in improving the billing systems
of recently-privatised telephone companies whose customers have up to now
received only rudimentary accounts with little information on individual
calls.
Mr Don Hayes, president of GTE Data Services, a subsidiary, said yesterday
that government-owned utilities 'haven't been motivated to be responsive to
the customer'.
GTE Data Services already has contracts in the Netherlands, Denmark and
Puerto Rico. Mr Hayes said the company was also in discussions with British
Telecom, an Italian phone company, and the Mexican telephone utility.
Bell, a unit of BCE Inc of Montreal, has been looking for ways to forge
links with foreign telecommunications companies as the domestic market
becomes more competitive.
</TEXT>
