FT  07 OCT 92 / DTI seeks winding up of travel agency
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By MICHAEL SKAPINKER
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
TRAVEL PREMIUMS Incor-porated, the UK subsidiary of a US company, closed its
London office last month, cancelling the holidays of up to 800 customers who
paid in advance, the Department of Trade and Industry said yesterday.
The DTI said Mr Michael Heseltine, trade and industry secretary, had
presented a petition to the High Court to wind up the company, which was
formed in 1990 and traded in the UK as a travel agent.
The official receiver was appointed provisional liquidator by the court
pending determination of the petition, which is expected to be heard in
December. The DTI said the petition had been presented 'to protect the
public interest from further harm'.
Trading standards officers in Richmond, south-west London, said they had
been receiving complaints about the company for more than three years. It
ceased trading on September 18.
The DTI said that customers should write to the official receiver at 21
Bloomsbury Street, London WC1B 3SS, or telephone 071-637 6559.
</TEXT>
