<HEADLINE>
FT  07 OCT 92 / BA launches Pounds 80m investment programme
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
BRITISH AIRWAYS yesterday launched a Pounds 80m investment programme aimed
at improving its transcontinental business class and Concorde services.
The revamp, which is the first for five years, will include eight-channel
personal video screens, more spacious seats and better lounge facilities for
those travelling business class.
BA, with other large airlines, has been hit during the recession by
companies sending their executives by economy class rather than business
class.
BA's passenger numbers have risen by 8.7 per cent this year compared with
figures for last year, which were hit by the Gulf war.
However, the growth has been mainly among economy-class passengers. Many of
these passengers are on heavily discounted tickets.
Under the re-launch, BA plans to refit all 6,000 of its business-class seats
on its fleet of 71 long-haul aircraft over the next year.
</TEXT>
