<HEADLINE>
FT  07 OCT 92 / Longer leading index falls
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
BRITAIN'S longer leading index, which pinpoints turning points in economic
activity 10 months in advance by tracking a number of different economic
indicators, fell for the third consecutive month in August, suggesting that
the recovery is not yet under way.
The shorter leading index, which highlights turning points about four months
in advance, suggests more optimistic prospects for the economy. It has risen
steadily since the beginning of the year.
The Central Statistical Office said the 0.3 per cent fall in the longer
leading indicator mainly reflected a fall in share prices.
