FT  07 OCT 92 / Barclays card unit to help debtors
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By DAVID BARCHARD
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
BARCLAYCARD, the card payments arm of Barclays, plans to help set up a new
consumer debt counselling service with a network of up to 25 centres
covering 90 per cent of the UK population, David Barchard writes.
The scheme is modelled on the US National Foundation for Consumer Credit in
Houston, Texas.
Debtors will be given help in arranging repayment programmes to clear their
problem loans over agreed periods of up to four years by paying the credit
counselling service a fixed amount each month.
The service then shares the payment out between an individual's creditors.
Barclaycard says that, unlike other debt-counselling services which have to
be maintained through donations, this one will fund itself through
contributions from creditors linked to debt repayment.
