<HEADLINE>
FT  07 OCT 92 / Dublin approves job threat fund
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By TIM COONE
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   DUBLIN
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
The Irish government last night approved an IPounds 50m (Pounds 46m) 'Market
Development Fund' to protect an estimated 30,000 jobs in Ireland's
manufacturing industry that have been placed at risk by sterling's
devaluation, writes Tim Coone in Dublin.
The fund will be allocated to companies which have a significant share of
their exports going to the UK market, or in the domestic or third country
markets in which they face competition from UK companies.
Payments will be made at the rate of IPounds 50 per week per employee, and
is expected to last until March 1993.
