FT  06 OCT 92 / UK Company News: C&amp;J Clark agrees to detailed takeover talks
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By PEGGY HOLLINGER
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
THE BOARD of C&amp;J Clark, the UK's biggest shoe manufacturer, has agreed to
detailed talks over a possible bid from a consortium comprised of Electra
Investment Trust and Specialist Research Unit, a firm of consultants.
SRU, which has been associated with Clark for more than 25 years, approached
Electra Investment Trust some weeks ago about backing a possible bid.
Clark said the talks were centred on a price 'substantially more than Pounds
100m.'
The discussions have been welcomed by the Clark board as 'friendly and
constructive'.
Electra has previously said it would not back a hostile offer.
Clark said it would be 'helpful' if the discussions could be settled before
its extraordinary general meeting on October 16.
That is when shareholders will vote on resolutions calling for the
resignation of Mr Walter Dickson, chairman, and another director.
The resolutions were put forward by a minority group of family shareholders
dissatisfied with corporate strategy and falling profits.
Clark is some 70 per cent held by more than 500 family members and six of
the 11 directors belong to the Clark family.
Mr Colin Fisher, managing director of SRU, is well known to the Clark board.
If SRU decides to make an offer, it is likely that Mr Fisher would be given
a place on the board.
Any successful offer is unlikely, however, to result in wider board changes.
</TEXT>
