FT  06 OCT 92 / International Company News: Citibank reshapes German
interests
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By ALAN FRIEDMAN
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   NEW YORK
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
CITIBANK, the leading US bank, said it would reorganise its German banking
interests into one new bank holding company in preparation for stricter
capital adequacy rules that take effect next year.
Until now the interests in Citibank's three German units have been split
between holding companies in the US and Germany.
The new holding company - Citibank Beteiligungen - will include the former
Citibank AG banking business in Frankfurt, Citibank Privatkunden, the
private banking division in Dusseldorf, and Citicorp Kartenservice, the
credit card business in Frankfurt.
